        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): deep-merge openai-codex plugin entry when openai already exists",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #93891\n\nWhen `plugins.entries.openai` already exists alongside the legacy `openai-codex` entry, `rewritePluginEntries` would silently delete the legacy entry without merging its config — losing fields like `baseUrl`, `reasoningEffort`, etc.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe original code only handled the single-key case (legacy-only). When both keys existed, it skipped the assignment branch and fired `delete` unconditionally, dropping all legacy fields.\n\n## Change\n\n`src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-config-migrations.runtime.providers.ts` — +31 lines\n\nAdded `deepMergePluginEntry` helper that recursively merges legacy keys into the canonical entry, with canonical winning on true conflicts. This mirrors the behavior that `migrateLegacyOpenAICodexProvider` already implements for the model-level equivalent.\n\n### Before\n```ts\n// input: {openai:{config:{embeddingModel:\"text-embedding-3-large\"}}, \"openai-codex\":{config:{baseUrl:\"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex\", reasoningEffort:\"high\"}}}\n// after rewritePluginEntries:\n// ❌ {openai:{config:{embeddingModel:\"text-embedding-3-large\"}}} — baseUrl + reasoningEffort gone\n```\n\n### After\n```ts\n// ✅ {openai:{config:{embeddingModel:\"text-embedding-3-large\", baseUrl:\"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex\", reasoningEffort:\"high\"}}}\n```\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93891-Bug-rewritePluginEntries-sile",
